nability by showing which features (e.g., texture, edge contrast) contribute most to uncertainty at boundary pixels, enhancing trust and transparency. This framework has broad applications in medical imaging, remote sensing, and robotics, where decisions depend heavily on accurate spatial understanding under uncertainty. By making uncertainty actionable and intent-aware, our method shifts the paradigm from passive uncertainty display to active semantic steering, empowering users to navigate the reliability-coverage trade-off interactively.",
